animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Iggy is the most adorable little guy. He loves to cuddle with his litter mates and his human. He is already doing well with potty pads! He hardly ever has an oopsie! He's very even tempered and loves to play with his toys. He likes to give kisses and hugs. He's very food motivated, and is very smart, so training him should go well! His foster mom and dad have 3 very big dogs as well as grandkids in the home too! Iggy has never met a stranger The video shows him and his brother Jagger eating together, it's too cute!

========================================================

Please contact
app@aarfhouston.org
for more information about this dog. You can apply online by clicking on Application .

Puppies
that are under 4 months old cannot be adopted outside of our Veterinary Service area. Please call for specific locations.

Children under 8 years old
often are not a good match for our puppies and dogs. In order to protect both, your child and our rescued dogs/puppies from harm, we seldom if ever adopt to families with young children.

Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue!

The adoption fee includes vaccinations, Bordetella, de-worming, rabies, spay/neuter and microchip. There is a an additional $12.99 fee for Home Again for a lifetime registration of the microchip.
Puppies cannot be adopted outside of the Houston area until they are spay/neutered after they are 4 months old. It is against the law in the State of Texas for a rescue not to be sterilized so we have to make sure it gets completed and that we have record of it.
NOTE: In our bios, we provide information based on our volunteer's experience with a particular dog; such as temperament, training, and ability to get along with others.
AARF is a 501(c)3 Non Profit, all breed, no kill organization. Our group is always in need of donations in order to continue to give the needed medical care to our rescues. Adoption fees do not begin to cover all of the medical costs. Any donation , no matter how small is a big help and is greatly appreciated. Please help us to continue to help them. Thank you.

animal.description:
Emse is a gorgeous, playful, healthy Treeing Walker Coon Hound who came to us with her siblings when their family realized they were in over their heads. We don't know much about their individual personalities, but they are a happy, healthy group of pups.

Please do your research before applying for any of these pups. TWC's are wonderful dogs, but require a great deal of energy and training. Like all hounds, they are very vocal and can be very loud. They are working dogs and can have a high prey drive. This is a good basic source of info: https://dogtime.com/dog-breeds/treeing-walker-coonhound#/slide/1


Most of our dogs require a fully fenced yard, this does depend on the individual dogs needs and safety requirements.  

Our dogs are fed a nutrient rich dog food.  Our experience is a high quality dog food keeps vet bills down and well-being high.

If you have any questions please email: claudiaatwag@gmail.com

Visit our website to fill out an Adoption Application  http://www.wagsequimwa.com

Adoption donation fee $400  (Please understand this adoption donation goes towards helping all the dogs we rescue)

animal.description:
Sweet, smart, & ready to spread her wings!

Shortly after giving birth, Lady Bird was abandoned in the Heights before being rescued and brought in to FFL. She has since recovered in foster care and can’t wait to settle in with her new family!

Lady Bird is sure to impress with her smart nature and eagerness to learn. She quickly catches on to new commands and currently knows how to sit, stay, lay down, up, and shake! She is fully housetrained and comfortable in a crate, and she’s very well behaved overall.

Her favorite activities include snuggling, going on walks, playing with toys (especially her soccer ball!), and playing fetch. With lots of energy, Lady Bird is assertive with other pups but knows when to respect others’ boundaries, so she’d do great with a friendly playmate!

Ready to meet Lady Bird? She’s ready to meet you!

animal.description:
Meet Starr! Starr is a very important pup here Charleston Animal Society.

In the beginning of December, we took in a transfer of 15 dogs, including Starr, from the Bahamas. All of these dogs have displayed under socialized and fearful behavior. From this transfer there are four dogs left. We are looking for a patient adopter who has a background in handling a dog with these types of anxieties and who can create a safe environment. This adopter has to understand these dogs can be a flight risk, they are sensitive to noises and hesitant to approach people. They are also looking for a home with a confident helper dog. Any potential adopter willing to open their home and hearts to any of these four dogs please reach out to the Charleston Animal Society Behavior Team to set up a meet and greet. (843) 327-1527 or email behavior@charlestonanimalsociety.org

animal.description:
Meet Radley!!!

This handsome Texas Boy came all the way up here to Wisconsin from Texas.

He is still working on his potty training but is getting hang of it. He stays quiet when being crated at nights. He is very very submissive and very friendly!!! He did great with our 12 and 10 years old kids. Did awesome with our resident dogs. No cats though! He may be shy at first but then he would give you many kisses as he can. He loves people!

Radley is neutered and up to date on vaccinations. He is a year old and is 40.8 pounds. 

Are you the right family for this handsome boy?! Please apply at this link:

https://www.cognitoforms.com/TinyPawsSmallDogRescue1/AdoptionApplication

Being fostered in Racine, WI.
Adoption Fee: $350.00
Email or text Amber with any questions: ladybugald@yahoo.com or 262-930-8937 (text only)

animal.description:
MEET YOHAN!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4499381.

Just look at Yohan's beautiful eyes and happy face! It's amazing that he's still smiling when he's been at the shelter for more than 60 days now. All of the volunteers have stated that they love taking him for a walk. He's very easy to take out of his kennel and walks easily on the leash. He does like to zig zag side-to-side when he's walking but once you know that, it's easy to get used to. He seeks attention from the volunteers and loves to be petted. He also knows "sit" for treats and takes them gently.

The one thing that Yohan doesn't like is other dogs. He will pull on the leash when he sees other dogs so he definitely has to be the only dog in the home. Yohan should not be taken to a dog park unless he's the only dog there. The shelter recommends that he goes to a home with older children (12+ years old).

Yohan needs an adopter that understands his only dog needs. If you think you can give Yohan the home that he needs, please come and meet him today! He's been at the shelter for a long time now and he's ready to go home!!

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description:
Sky / Female / 1 Year / 52 lbs / American Bulldog Mix / Toronto

Meet Sky! Sky comes to us all the way from Hohenwald, Tennessee! When her owner was no longer able to care for her, Sky was left abandoned in their home. The local Sheriff had to go inside to rescue this gentle girl, and she happily went with him towards her new life. Once she was cleared to travel, Sky made the long drive to Canada in search of her forever family!

Since being in foster care, Sky has shown everyone just how loving she is. She adores affection and snuggling up close to her humans. She is well behaved, mellow, sweet, gentle and loyal. She loves to be talked to and her ears will perk right up so you know she’s listening. When she’s not chewing her bones or getting belly rub, Sky loves to play fetch with her favorite tennis ball. Sky would do best with a family who is home more often than not and will include her in daily activities.

Sky is friendly and loving with people she knows. She tends to follow her family as they move throughout the house - she likes to be close. With new people she is quite shy and may growl or bark to ask for space. When she is warming up she should be ignored and her personal space respected. Once she can eliminate any threat, she will come around for a sniff. Adopters should have realistic expectations when meeting her, as it will take time to earn her trust.

Sky has confinement anxiety, so she does not like her crate. When attempting to crate her she was under extreme distress, and posed a risk to herself. She prefers to be left in a puppy proofed space where she feels safe and comfortable. If she is given enough exercise prior to being alone, she may whine a little but settles eventually. Adopters will need to have a flexible schedule and be able to support her through this.

Sky works well on leash, she is very cooperative and attentive to her people. She doesn’t pull unless she sees a squirrel or something she wants to chase. She gets bored with walks around the same block, but gets very excited when she finds a new route! She doesn’t know many commands yet but is very trainable and eager to learn. She is nervous of strange dogs and people, so socialization should be an ongoing focus.

Sky’s ideal family would have at least one family member who is home most of the time. Adopters will need to have some dog experience and be comfortable working through her seperation anxiety. She would be overwhelmed in the city so would prefer homes in the suburbs or quiet country. She would do best with a detached house, with a full fenced back yard. Sky has not been tested with dogs or cats while in foster care. Based on her disposition, she would likely do well with calm and respectful children that are ages 10+.

If you’re interested in adopting Sky please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Sky’s adoption fee is $800. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.
